The challenge with anime series is trying to convince someone who's never
seen any of it to purchase it.  This is further complicated by the problem
that ADV does single-disc releases first, then does a complete boxset once
the series is finished.  The boxset is like 60% less than the individual
discs - thus screwing the diehard fans who bought the single discs in the
first place.  This is why I never buy ANY anime until I get that
discounted boxset.  But, then, what about shows I've never heard of?  It's
one thing to take a gamble on a $20 disc, but a whole series for $60-80?

The other thing I don't understand the reason I would  buy on DVD is to
get the show in its original format - that being uncut, spoken Japanese (with
English subtitles).  If ADV starts hawking editted-for-the-US-market DVDs,
then they'll lose me entirely as a customer.

