For me, here is my ideal world wrt US companies and their anime
distribution policies (esp online anime).

- The first four episodes of any given TV series are offered on an
online service for free (free subscription is fine). Smallish and VHS
quality (watchable, but not great). I wouldn't ever use bit torrent
for anime again if they would ever offer some kind of reasonable
*preview* of their properties (1.5min music videos don't count).

- Then, if you like the show, you can:
1) buy the DVDs (or HD or Blu, whatever) off the shelf, or
2) you can pay a % fee of the DVD (or whatever) cost to watch it
online instead. Or whatever black-box hardware the service would
provide you when you subscribe to it -- select an episode and the
hardware spits out a freshly burned DVD or whatever

